                            <comment id="14970578" author="eduard.vodicka@eforce21.com" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2015 07:24:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A workaround that keeps a strong reference to the CoordinationHolder as long as it is not passed to the client solves the problem. A possible solution is demonstrated in the attached patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14989011" author="cziegeler" created="Wed, 4 Nov 2015 06:45:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eduard.vodicka%40eforce21.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eduard.vodicka@eforce21.com&quot;&gt;eduard.vodicka@eforce21.com&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for reporting this and providing a patch. I&apos;ve committed a slightly different fix in rev 1712478. Could you please verify if it fixes your problem?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14991960" author="eduard.vodicka@eforce21.com" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 16:50:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I could not reproduce the problem in my tests anymore. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
